text: Henri Auguste Arnaud (16 April 1891 – 14 February 1956) was a French middle- distance runner who was part of the French team at the 1912 Summer Olympics.https://www.olympic.org/henri-auguste-arnaud He reached the finals of the men's 1500 metres race, but did not win a medal. ==References== Category:1891 births Category:1956 deaths Category:Olympic athletes of France Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 1912 Summer Olympics Category:French male middle-distance runners
title: Henri Arnaud (athlete)
